Kenya to Spend 9.6 Billion Shillings to Help Alleviate Drought

-- B y   J o h n s t o n e   O l e   T u r a n a
-- 
2011-02-21T06:14:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/kenya-to-spend-9-6-billion-shillings-to-help-alleviate-impact-of-drought.html
Kenya will spend 9.6 billion
shillings ($117.4 million) to help alleviate the effects of a
drought in the East African country, a Special Programmes
Ministry official said.  The government allocated 1.1 billion shillings to the
purchase of livestock in drought-stricken areas, Andrew Mondoh,
permanent secretary in the ministry, told reporters today in
Nairobi, the capital.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Johnstone Ole Turana in Nairobi at 
 jturana@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  